This paper is primarily focused on computer vision-based localization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a fully convolutional network (FCN) for feature extraction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of robotics applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of image processing techniques, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
